
[1]brilliant

   BRILL'IANT, a. [Eng. beryl and pearl.]

   1. Sparkling with luster; glittering; as a brilliant gem; a brilliant
   dress.

   2. Splendid; shining; as a brilliant achievement.

   Washington was more solicitous to avoid fatal mistakes,than to perform
   brilliant exploits.

    BRILL'IANT, n. A diamond of the finest cut, formed into angles, so as
       to refract the light, by which it is rendered more glittering.

   1. In the manege, a brisk,high-spirited horse,with a stately carriage.
